			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Obtaining Your Disciplines<a name="52680"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 19 04 4:04 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Ok, theres two ways to go about this.
<br />

<br />
1) Open your combat abilities window. Should see 8 squares below it for hotkeys. RIGHT-click on a box and it should bring up a little pop-up with 5 pull-out boxes. These pull-outs represent the different timers each disc resides on. Within these pull-outs you can find your discs, select one and a hotkey will be set into the box you right clicked.
<br />

<br />
2) There is a little box on the default combat abilities window with a 'c' in it. Left clicking that will bring up a window that looks like your skills window with all your combat abilities/discs on it. Select the skill you want to use and click the &quot;make hotkey&quot; button to create a hotkey. You can then treat this as a regular hotkey or you can put it into your combat ability boxes.
<br />

<br />
I used both of the above to setup my discs, like FM.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=844375">Reilna Voiceofwar</A><br>

"Be a bard's bard!"</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
